		<h2>Inversion of Control</h2>

		<p>
			NerdyForms comes out of the box wired for dependency injection and inversion of control - simply register your form handler that implements <code>INerdyFormHandler</code>
			and let the container of your choice do the wiring for you!.
		</p>

		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-12">
				<h3>Example Using SimpleInjector</h3>
				<pre><code>protected void Application_Start()
{
	Container tContainer = new Container();

	tContainer.Register&lt;NerdyFormHandler, InMemoryNerdyFormHandler&gt;();

	tContainer.RegisterMvcControllers(Assembly.GetExecutingAssembly());
	tContainer.RegisterMvcIntegratedFilterProvider();

	tContainer.Verify();

	DependencyResolver.SetResolver(new SimpleInjectorDependencyResolver(tContainer));
					
	RouteTable.Routes.MapRoute(
		name: "NerdyForms",
		url: "Form/{FormName}",
		defaults: new { controller = "NerdyForm", action = "Handle" }
	);
}</code></pre>

